<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Raised Bed on Jérémie Litzler</title><link>https://iamjeremie.me/tags/raised-bed/</link><description>Recent content in Raised Bed on Jérémie Litzler</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 13 Nov 2022 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://iamjeremie.me/tags/raised-bed/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Create a no dig raised bed, compost on weeds, with tips on planting and see the growth, by Charles Dowding</title><link>https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/create-a-no-dig-raised-bed-charles-dowding/</link><pubDate>Sun, 13 Nov 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://iamjeremie.me/post/2022-11/create-a-no-dig-raised-bed-charles-dowding/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://iamjeremie.me/images/2022-11-13-a-raised-bed-with-a-pile-of-compost-with-a-wheel-barrow-in-the-background.jpg" alt="Featured image of post Create a no dig raised bed, compost on weeds, with tips on planting and see the growth, by Charles Dowding" />&lt;p>Creating a raised bed with no dig is easy. Let&amp;rsquo;s look how it is done.&lt;/p>
&lt;!-- raw HTML omitted -->
&lt;p>Thanks to Charles Dowding for sharing his wisdom and knowledge! I wrote the following notes watching the video published on Charles Dowding&amp;rsquo;s channel. You can watch it using &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OIojWdJz0RE">this YouTube link&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="materials">Materials&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>You will need to:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>two pieces of wood: 2.4 meters long, 5 cm thick and 15 cm tall.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>eight screws in stainless steel of 80 mm in length.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="construction-instructions">Construction instructions&lt;/h2>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Cut in half each piece of piece of wood&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Drill 2.5cm deep holes on one end only of the 1.2 m long wood pieces.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;p>
